No-one will contradict you there.

41
00:03:47,090 --> 00:03:49,840
苏珊・弗林特夏尔偷了妈妈的女仆
Susan Flintshire has stolen Mama's maid

42
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:52,100
她女儿还在我们家作客呢
whilst her daughter's a guest in this house?

43
00:03:52,210 --> 00:03:53,640
她肯定不会这么说
I'm sure she wouldn't put it like that.

44
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:57,180
我管她怎么说  这太下作了
I don't care how she puts it. It's absolutely disgraceful.

45
00:03:58,970 --> 00:04:02,170
-没事  玛姬和我说了  -当然有事
- It's all right. Madge told me. - It is NOT all right.

46
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:05,060
-你真毫不知情吗  -不知道
- Did you have any idea? - No. Not really.

47
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,970
我知道  妈妈觉得
I knew, I knew that Mummy

48
00:04:06,970 --> 00:04:09,900
奥布瑞恩很会做头发
thought O'Brien was very good at doing hair,

49
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:11,850
他们还说过  奥布瑞恩想去旅行
and they talked about her wanting to travel...

50
00:04:11,850 --> 00:04:15,540
-什么时候  -你们在唐伊阁的时候
- What? When? - When you were all at Duneagle.

51
00:04:15,810 --> 00:04:17,550
你竟然没告诉我们
And you didn't think to inform us?

52
00:04:17,550 --> 00:04:20,850
我明天去伦敦  可以在《女士》杂志上登则广告
I'm in London tomorrow. I can put an advertisement in The Lady.

53
00:04:20,850 --> 00:04:21,950
很好
Good.

54
00:04:22,620 --> 00:04:26,270
等杂志刊登信息会不会要很久
Won't it take forever, waiting for the magazine to come out?

55
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:27,740
这也没办法
It can't be helped.

56
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:29,200
我们十一点要见特伦特
We're meeting Trent at eleven.

57
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:32,460
到时见  我想先去种植园走走
I'll see you there. I want to walk the plantations first.

58
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:34,800
不知道玛丽想不想一起去
I was wondering if Mary might like to come.

59
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:38,270
别打扰玛丽  她够烦的了
Don't bother Mary. She's got enough on her plate.

60
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:43,440
你真的什么都不知道
Did you really not know anything?

61
00:04:44,770 --> 00:04:46,630
我没想到她真会这么做
I never thought she'd go through with it.

62
00:04:51,590 --> 00:04:53,800
我想您该带上这件
I thought you might like to take this down with you.

63
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:56,700
要是您想出去走走  外头挺冷的
In case you want a walk. It's quite chilly.

64
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:58,100
黑色那件呢
Where's the black one?

65
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:07,990
我带乔治少爷去散散步  小姐
I'm taking Master George out for some air, m'lady,

66
00:05:07,990 --> 00:05:10,430
您要一起来吗
and I wondered if you'd like to come with us.

67
00:05:10,430 --> 00:05:13,840
不了  谢谢
I don't think so, but thank you.

68
00:05:14,510 --> 00:05:16,040
可怜的小孤儿
Poor little orphan.

69
00:05:18,290 --> 00:05:19,710
谢谢  保姆
Thank you, Nanny.

70
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:28,640
他不是孤儿  他有母亲
He's not an orphan. He's got his mother.

71
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,910
孤儿没有
Orphans haven't.

72
00:05:29,910 --> 00:05:32,360
要这么说  他也不可怜[穷]
He isn't poor either, come to that.

73
00:05:35,090 --> 00:05:38,010
您不介意我照顾夫人吧
And you don't mind my seeing to her ladyship?

74
00:05:38,010 --> 00:05:42,140
为何介意  我又没打算环游世界
Why would I mind? I'm not planning a trip round the world.

75
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:56,260
莫斯利先生  你看见崔维斯先生了吗
Mr Molesley. Have you seen Mr Travis?

76
00:05:56,310 --> 00:05:59,520
我要和他谈慈善集市的事
I need to speak to him about the Bring and Buy Sale.

77
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,650
没见着  夫人
I'm afraid not, your ladyship.

78
00:06:02,540 --> 00:06:03,760
好吧
Never mind.

79
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:08,170
真是令人伤感啊
This were a sad business.

80
00:06:08,860 --> 00:06:10,550
悲伤之极
Very, very sad.

81
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:13,930
真不敢相信  已经到立碑的时候了
I can't believe it's time for the stone already.

82
00:06:13,930 --> 00:06:15,250
六个月了
Six months.

83
00:06:15,270 --> 00:06:18,150
安顿坟墓需要六个月
They always leave six months for the grave to settle.

84
00:06:21,170 --> 00:06:24,360
你儿子找到新工作了吗
Tell me has, has your son found another job, yet?

85
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,370
没  夫人
No, m'lady.

86
00:06:25,370 --> 00:06:26,430
他们留下他了
They've let him stay on

87
00:06:26,430 --> 00:06:29,010
他也总是很努力
and he always tries to make himself useful,

88
00:06:29,010 --> 00:06:31,290
但也不能长久如此
but it can't go on forever

89
00:06:31,740 --> 00:06:33,480
而且  他还没了薪水
and anyway, he's lost his wage.

90
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:35,490
但他是个训练有素的贴身男仆
But he's a properly trained valet.

91
00:06:35,780 --> 00:06:37,350
还可以当个管家
He could even be a butler.

92
00:06:37,350 --> 00:06:39,050
我倒希望如此  夫人
I hope so, m'lady...

93
00:06:41,180 --> 00:06:43,260
但世道多变啊
..But it's a changing world.

94
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,200
这点我清楚得很
You don't have to tell me.

95
00:06:54,870 --> 00:06:56,280
你好啊
Hello.

96
00:06:58,070 --> 00:07:00,940
你很快就能走路了  小姐
It'll soon be time for you to get out and walk, young lady.

97
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:04,400
请不要在未经我允许的情况下碰这孩子
Please don't touch the children, not without my permission.

98
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:05,520
什么
What?

99
00:07:05,580 --> 00:07:08,780
照看他们是我的责任  再小心也不为过
They are in my charge and I cannot be too careful.

100
00:07:09,690 --> 00:07:12,820
你可别忘了  我认识这孩子的母亲
I would remind you that I knew this young girl's mother,

101
00:07:12,820 --> 00:07:14,400
跟你不一样
which you never did.

102
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,670
那并不代表你是她的朋友
That doesn't make you her friend.

103
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:18,420
我确实是她的朋友
As a matter of fact, it does.

104
00:07:18,430 --> 00:07:22,480
我没时间跟你拌嘴
Well, I can't stay here to bandy words.

105
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:24,120
你能不能转告帕特莫太太
Will you ask Mrs Patmore

106
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:27,010
让她在半小时内备好孩子的午餐
to send up the children's luncheon in half an hour?

107
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:29,720
你自己跟她说吧
Ask her yourself, why don't you?

108
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:37,850
夫人是不是很失望
Was her ladyship very disappointed?

109
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:42,410
是  而且得一阵子才能找到合适的人选
She was, and it'll take quite a while to find a replacement.

110
00:07:42,410 --> 00:07:44,990
真没想到奥布瑞恩小姐这么欠考虑
I can't believe Miss O'Brien would be so thoughtless.

111
00:07:44,990 --> 00:07:46,840
出乎意料吗  我倒不觉得
Can't you? I can.

112
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:49,290
她想出去冒险  这有什么不妥的
She wants an adventure. What's wrong with that?

113
00:07:49,530 --> 00:07:50,250
反正我不怪她
I don't blame her.

114
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:51,230
她可以离开
Not for wanting to go,

115
00:07:51,230 --> 00:07:53,340
但别突然就跑了  让大家措手不及
but why run off and leave us in the lurch?

116
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:55,970
你这么说是想让大家觉得你事先也不知情吧
You're talking like that so we'll think you didn't know.

117
00:07:55,970 --> 00:07:57,550
怎么能这么说呢
That's not kind!

118
00:07:57,550 --> 00:08:01,160
拉着个脸有什么用  祝她好运
What's the good of a month of sour looks? Good luck to her.

119
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:04,090
-玛丽小姐今早怎么样  -还是老样子
- How was Lady Mary this morning? - The same.

120
00:08:04,230 --> 00:08:06,700
她最终会走出来吧
But, I suppose she must come out of it eventually.

121
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,090
起码也要为乔治少爷考虑一下
For Master George's sake, if for no other reason.

122
00:08:09,090 --> 00:08:10,030
但愿如此
I hope so.

123
00:08:10,630 --> 00:08:13,100
她现在把一切都交给维斯特保姆了
Right now, she prefers to leave it all to Nanny West.

124
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:14,340
保姆的工作我可做不来
I couldn't be a nanny.

125
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:16,330
为什么  你不喜欢孩子吗
Why not? Don't you like children?

126
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:17,550
喜欢是喜欢
No, I do.

127
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:18,790
但做了保姆的话
Being a nanny

128
00:08:18,790 --> 00:08:20,840
既不算家里人  又不算仆人
you're not one of the family but not one of us either.

129
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:23,770
-你们在聊什么呢  -做保姆
- What are you talking about? - Being a nanny.

130
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:26,810
黛西说那种生活一定很孤独
Daisy was saying she thinks it must be a lonely life.

131
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:27,930
这我倒不知道
I don't know about that.

132
00:08:27,930 --> 00:08:30,870
不过要我说  那个维斯特保姆实在是自恃过高了
But if you ask me, that Nanny West thinks too much of herself.

133
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:33,940
她怎么了  她一向对我挺好的
Why? What's she done? She always seems nice to me.

134
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:35,840
她就会对我颐指气使
She only tried to give me orders.

135
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:38,080
你是说她把你当成仆人了
You mean she mistook you for a servant?

136
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,170
-但他就是个仆人  -这话可别跟他说
- But he IS a servant. - Don't tell him that.

137
00:08:40,170 --> 00:08:42,200
他可承受不了这个打击
He'll never get over the shock!

138
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,770
多谢了  马什先生
Thank you, Mr Marsh.

139
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:51,410
他失望也在所难免
He was bound to be disappointed.

140
00:08:51,420 --> 00:08:53,550
你真的要放弃整个计划吗
You're really sure you want to abandon the whole plan?

141
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:55,140
我们别无选择
We don't have a choice.

142
00:08:55,730 --> 00:08:58,030
有一半的地产都要缴继承税
We have to find the death duties on half the estate.

143
00:08:58,040 --> 00:09:00,210
-后果一定不堪设想  -我知道
- And they'll be merciless. - I know.

144
00:09:00,310 --> 00:09:02,710
不过我希望我们能等玛丽回来参与处理这事
But, I wish we could wait for Mary to come back into play.

145
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:04,320
这本来就不关她的事
She isn't a player.

146
00:09:04,420 --> 00:09:08,540
她生前可以享有马修在唐顿
She has a life interest in one third of Matthew's share of Downton,

147
00:09:08,540 --> 00:09:10,060
和其他地方财产的三分之一
and a third of his other possessions,

148
00:09:10,060 --> 00:09:12,410
但其他的财产都归乔治所有
but everything else belongs to little George.

149
00:09:12,410 --> 00:09:13,900
法律规定她只能继承这么一点吗  
And that's all the law gives her?

150
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:15,800
他该起草一份遗嘱的
He should have made a will.

151
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:17,730
但玛丽是乔治的监护人
But, Mary's George's guardian.

152
00:09:17,730 --> 00:09:19,910
这难道不能给她点话语权吗
Surely that gives her some sort of say?

153
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:21,380
说不准
It's a moot point.

154
00:09:21,690 --> 00:09:23,560
既然所有财产的一半都归我所有
Since I own the other half of everything,

155
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:27,260
由我来管理孩子的财产不是更合适吗
isn't it more appropriate for me to manage the boy's fortunes?

156
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:30,640
更何况她现在这么脆弱
Besides, she's in such a fragile state,

157
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:33,470
我真不想让她为财产的事烦心
the last thing I want is for her to start worrying about money.

158
00:09:33,470 --> 00:09:35,850
话虽这么说  但您不觉得...  
Of course. But you don't think...?

159
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:37,190
你知道她是什么样子
You've seen her!

160
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:40,650
她连吃饭的力气都没有
She hardly has the energy to lift a fork to her mouth.

161
00:09:40,650 --> 00:09:42,270
她很爱他
She loved him very much.

162
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:45,900
真爱的代价就是其中一方之死所带来的巨大痛苦
And the price of great love is great misery when one of you dies.

163
00:09:47,130 --> 00:09:49,230
-我知道  -是的
- I know that. - Of course you do.

164
00:09:49,230 --> 00:09:50,650
真抱歉
I'm so sorry.

165
00:09:51,330 --> 00:09:54,210
咱们快点回去吧  别耽误了吃午饭
We better get back or we'll be late for lunch.

166
00:09:59,570 --> 00:10:02,260
您知道我登了广告的  卡森先生
I've placed advertisements, Mr Carson, you know I have.

167
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:05,950
-没有合适的吗  -根本没有回音
- But the answers weren't suitable? - I didn't get any answers.

168
00:10:05,950 --> 00:10:09,270
倒不是完全没有  但我回信之后就没有回音了
Well, I did, but when I wrote back, I heard nothing more.

169
00:10:09,270 --> 00:10:12,270
我不知该说些什么了
Well, I don't know what to suggest.

170
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:16,830
因为  我不能留在这吗
Because, I can't stay here?

171
00:10:16,830 --> 00:10:21,240
莫斯利先生  我不想显得无理
Mr Molesley, I should hate us to appear inhospitable.

172
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:22,540
但我不能留在这儿
But I can't stay here.

173
00:10:22,540 --> 00:10:27,430
这对老爷来说公平吗  毕竟都六个月了
Is it fair on his lordship? It has been six months.

174
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:32,080
我可以去我爸爸那儿  再想办法
I suppose I could go to my dad's until I get something sorted.

175
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:33,770
好主意
What a good idea.

176
00:10:33,770 --> 00:10:37,150
-午饭准备好了  -谢谢你  帕特莫太太
- Servants' lunch is on the table. - Thank you, Mrs Patmore.

177
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:44,620
高兴点  莫斯利先生  事情还没定下来呢
Oh cheer up, Mr Molesley. It may never happen.

178
00:10:44,620 --> 00:10:46,060
已经成定局了
It already has.

179
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:52,300
我午餐后要去瑟斯克  你要一起去吗
By the way, I'm going into Thirsk after lunch. Do you want to come?

180
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:55,410
我要去村里  看看伊泽贝尔怎么样了
I'm walking down to the village to see how Isobel's getting on.

181
00:10:55,410 --> 00:10:57,180
跟她说  随时可以来
Remind her it's an open invitation,

182
00:10:57,180 --> 00:10:58,480
她要是想看看孙子
if she wants to see her grandson

183
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:01,030
或是想找人陪陪她  只要过来就行
or feels like company, she just has to turn up.

184
00:11:01,030 --> 00:11:01,980
我会转告她的
I'll tell her.

185
00:11:01,980 --> 00:11:04,880
-我可能会和你一起去  -还是别了
- I might come with you. - I don't think so.

186
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:06,850
我觉得她可能不想见到太多人
I don't think she's up to seeing many people.

187
00:11:06,850 --> 00:11:08,720
我只是想去村里而已
I only meant into the village.

188
00:11:09,070 --> 00:11:10,970
伊迪丝 你明天真的要去伦敦吗
Edith, are you really going to London tomorrow?

189
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:13,050
如果你去  我正好有事让你帮我办
I have a couple of errands if you are.

190
00:11:13,050 --> 00:11:14,910
我要去见迈克尔・格莱格森
I'm seeing Michael Gregson.

191
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:17,210
你留在这里的日子  他一定想死你了
He must have missed you while you've been here.

192
00:11:17,290 --> 00:11:20,970
他要举办一个宴会  把我介绍给他文学圈的朋友
He's giving a party to introduce me to his literary friends.

193
00:11:20,970 --> 00:11:23,890
真令人期待  是不是  罗伯特
How exciting. Isn't it, Robert?

194
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:40,560
我可不可以放一张卡片在你的橱窗里
I... I was wondering if I might put a card in your window.

195
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:43,820
-什么样的卡片  小姐  -工作招人的卡片
- A card, m'lady? - For a job asking for applicants.

196
00:11:43,820 --> 00:11:45,480
是什么样的工作呢
And what sort of job might this be?

197
00:11:45,490 --> 00:11:47,530
怎么  这还有什么区别吗
Why? Does it make a difference?

198
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,730
-不  并没有  -谢谢你了
- No, I suppose not. - Thank you.

199
00:11:50,730 --> 00:11:54,420
-我该付你多少钱呢  -六便士就好
- Erm, how much will that be? - Sixpence should cover it.

200
00:11:59,390 --> 00:12:01,480
你真应该多去看看乔治
You ought to see more of George.

201
00:12:02,670 --> 00:12:03,880
可怜的乔治
Poor George.

202
00:12:04,970 --> 00:12:07,020
一出生就命途多舛
What a burden he is born into.

203
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:11,670
身家阔绰  妈妈却形如枯槁
A baby rich as Croesus and a mother almost passed over.

204
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:12,980
法律就是如此
That's the law.

205
00:12:13,460 --> 00:12:15,180
感觉好奇怪
It seems so strange.

206
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:19,330
马修一向谨小慎微
Matthew was always so meticulous.

207
00:12:20,290 --> 00:12:23,540
他以为死亡离他还早得很
He thought that death was many years away.

208
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:25,700
本来也应该如此
And so it should have been.

209
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:31,390
如果有什么我能帮忙的  请尽管开口
If there's anything I can do to help, please let me do it.

210
00:12:32,660 --> 00:12:34,200
我很感激
I'm grateful.

211
00:12:39,770 --> 00:12:42,080
但是你看  如果你的独子过世了
But you see, when your only child dies...

212
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:46,790
你就不再是一个母亲了
..Then you're not a mother any more.

213
00:12:48,140 --> 00:12:49,870
你就什么也不是了
You're not anything, really.

214
00:12:51,810 --> 00:12:53,910
我在努力适应这一点
That's what I'm trying to get used to.

215
00:12:54,330 --> 00:12:55,800
你也是一位祖母
You're a grandmother.

216
00:12:56,970 --> 00:12:59,600
我知道你一定会是位出色的祖母
And I know you're going to be a wonderful one.

217
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:12,190
-下午送来的信  -谢谢
- Afternoon post. - Ah, thank you.

218
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:16,560
怎么又这样
Oh, not this again.

219
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:17,760
怎么了
Not what?

220
00:13:19,940 --> 00:13:22,660
没什么
Oh...nothing!

221
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:25,600
家具商来了就通知我一声
Let me know when the upholsterer arrives.

222
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:28,220
你布置工作的时候  我也要在场
I want to be there when you explain the job in hand.

223
00:13:28,220 --> 00:13:30,150
好呀  不过我一人就能办好了
Very well, but I can easily manage.

224
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:33,950
得让他知道挂毯有多贵重
He needs to grasp the quality of the tapestry on the chairs,

225
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:36,270
免得他冒冒失失地往上钉钉子
before he starts slamming nails into them.

226
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:38,690
难道我就交代不明白吗
And I couldn't make him see that?

227
00:14:06,850 --> 00:14:09,660
招工  贴身女仆  会女红和梳头

228
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:14,990
我们关门了  亲爱的
Just closing, love.

229
00:14:14,990 --> 00:14:17,900
我只想知道是谁在找贴身女仆
I only wanted to know who was looking for a lady's maid.

230
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:20,880
在唐顿  也只有那几个需要找贴身女仆的
There's not too many in Downton who need a lady's maid.

231
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:22,330
你是指庄园的人吗 
You mean the Abbey?

232
00:14:22,410 --> 00:14:24,160
你以前不是在那里干过吗
Didn't you used to work there?

233
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:28,040
我干过  但我后来去学东西了
I did, but I've been studying since then.

234
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:32,140
-学什么  -学习如何做贴身女仆
- Studying for what? - To become a lady's maid.

235
00:14:34,620 --> 00:14:39,570
玛姬说伊迪丝小姐下午去看望了卡劳利夫人
Madge says that Lady Edith saw Mrs Crawley this afternoon.

236
00:14:40,070 --> 00:14:43,560
-她还好吗  -恐怕是非常不好  
- How is she? - In a very dark place, I'm afraid.

237
00:14:43,630 --> 00:14:44,890
这也难怪
And no wonder.

238
00:14:45,820 --> 00:14:48,440
一个寡妇  又失去了独子
For a widowed mother to lose an only son...

239
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:51,480
没有比您更合适去安慰她的人了
There's no more fit person to comfort her than you.

240
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:52,890
是吗
I wonder.

241
00:14:53,420 --> 00:14:56,890
如果茜玻小姐是我的独女  我怕是活不下去了
If Lady Sybil had been an only child I believe I'd have died.

242
00:14:57,180 --> 00:15:01,220
不  夫人  您会为孩子好好活下去
No, m'lady. You would have lived on for the baby.

243
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:02,940
她也一样
And so must she.

244
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:10,460
谢谢你  休斯太太  晚安了
Thank you so much, Mrs Hughes, and good night to you.

245
00:15:10,740 --> 00:15:12,070
晚安  夫人
Good night, m'lady.

246
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,430
老爷
M'lord.

247
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:17,450
你还好吧
Are you all right?

248
00:15:17,810 --> 00:15:19,310
我觉得我们得定下来
I feel we must settle the question

249
00:15:19,310 --> 00:15:21,270
由谁来打理孩子的财产
of who is to manage the baby's property.

250
00:15:21,270 --> 00:15:24,220
我不想催促玛丽
I don't want to hurry Mary before she's ready.

251
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:25,500
这有什么可争论的
What question?

252
00:15:26,810 --> 00:15:28,560
她是乔治的妈妈和监护人啊
She's George's mother and his guardian.

253
00:15:28,570 --> 00:15:30,020
当然了
Of course she is,

254
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:33,550
但是涉及到关于庄园的决定
but when it comes to decisions about the estate,

255
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:34,850
我来不是更妥当吗
shouldn't it be me?

256
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:35,880
为什么
Why?

257
00:15:36,190 --> 00:15:40,550
因为我和我的外孙共同拥有六分之五的唐顿
Because, together, my grandson and I own five sixths of Downton.

258
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:42,370
而玛丽的部分只是有生之年享有
Mary's share is only for her life.

259
00:15:42,370 --> 00:15:44,870
即使她想  也做不了什么
She couldn't do much with it even if she wanted to.

260
00:15:46,380 --> 00:15:49,840
重要的是  因为遗传税的缘故
The point being that with the death duties we're facing,

261
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,420
我们要做出一些重要的决定
there are some big decisions ahead.

262
00:15:51,420 --> 00:15:52,830
你要把玛丽挤出去吗
You want to push Mary out.

263
00:15:52,830 --> 00:15:55,630
我不是要挤她  她本来也没有决定权
I'm not pushing her out. She was never "In."

264
00:15:56,050 --> 00:15:58,630
马修是共同所有人  如今他儿子是
Matthew was co-owner and now his son is.

265
00:15:58,630 --> 00:16:03,400
我曾跟马修共同努力  如今我要为他的儿子努力
I worked with Matthew. I must work for his boy.

266
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,130
谢谢
Thanks.

267
00:16:17,220 --> 00:16:19,390
周二居然有这么多信
A lot of letters for a Tuesday.

268
00:16:19,390 --> 00:16:22,780
这一周刚刚开始  大家哪来的时间写信啊
How do people have time to write when the week is just beginning?

269
00:16:22,780 --> 00:16:25,210
今天是情人节
It's Saint Valentine's Day.

270
00:16:25,210 --> 00:16:28,950
你居然记得这日子  而我却忘了
Oh, imagine your remembering that and my forgetting it.

271
00:16:28,950 --> 00:16:30,640
这谁能想得到啊
Who would have thought such a thing?

272
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:33,300
我也不是完全不懂浪漫
I am not a complete stranger to romance

273
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:35,270
如果你是这个意思的话
if that's what you're implying.

274
00:16:35,970 --> 00:16:39,700
或许现在是吧  但也不一直是如此
Maybe I am now, but I wasn't always.

275
00:16:42,290 --> 00:16:44,550
等等  我以为这都是账单呢
Hold on. I thought these were all bills.

276
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:47,170
黛茜  这封是给你的
Daisy! This one's for you.

277
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:50,860
黛茜  是谁寄的啊
Daisy? Who's that from?

278
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:52,850
别取笑她  巴罗先生
Don't tease her, Mr Barrow.

279
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:57,640
谁给你寄了卡片
Who sent you a card?

280
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:00,340
我也不知道  上面没有签名
I don't know. It's not signed.

281
00:17:00,340 --> 00:17:03,900
我的也是  看来我们俩都有暗恋者
Nor's mine. We both must have secret admirers.

282
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:06,070
这也不奇怪嘛
Which is no more than we deserve.

283
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:15,170
差不多行了  贝茨先生  还有活儿要干呢
That's enough of that, Mr. Bates. We've work to do.

284
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:31,080
看什么呢
What's that?

285
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,050
没什么
Nothing.

286
00:17:35,150 --> 00:17:38,090
是啊  今天是情人节
Of course. It's Valentine's Day.

287
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:41,920
你什么时候去伦敦
When are you leaving for London?

288
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,580
十点钟的火车
I'm catching the ten o'clock.

289
00:17:48,570 --> 00:17:49,990
我该去收拾了
I ought to pack.

290
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,510
玩得开心
Have a happy time.

291
00:18:15,450 --> 00:18:20,640
里彭  中央济贫院

292
00:18:33,890 --> 00:18:34,870
上帝是仁慈的

293
00:18:25,970 --> 00:18:27,190
就是那个
Just down there.

294
00:18:37,610 --> 00:18:38,880
格里格先生
Mr. Grigg?

295
00:18:42,690 --> 00:18:43,820
我们认识吗
Do I know you?

296
00:18:49,690 --> 00:18:52,510
你写信给唐顿庄园的查理・卡森
You wrote to Charlie Carson at Downton Abbey.

297
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:56,340
我们一起工作
I work with him.

298
00:18:57,110 --> 00:18:58,340
是他派你来的吗
Did he send you?

299
00:18:58,420 --> 00:19:01,470
也不尽然
Not exactly. In a way.

300
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:12,380
他都说我什么了
What... What did he say about me?

301
00:19:13,090 --> 00:19:14,470
他打算怎么办
What does he plan to do?

302
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:16,220
卡森先生是个大忙人
Mr. Carson is very busy.

303
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:19,330
他想让我来看看你现在情况如何
He wanted me to find out how you are.

304
00:19:19,330 --> 00:19:22,470
然后  他才能有所打算
Then, I think he'll come up with a plan.

305
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:24,530
我就知道
I knew it.

306
00:19:25,540 --> 00:19:27,960
上一次见面  他说了许多伤人的话
He said some harsh things when we last met,

307
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:31,690
但查理和我  我们交情很深
but, we go back a long way, Charlie and me.

308
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:34,010
所以无论发生什么
And whatever's happened,

309
00:19:34,870 --> 00:19:39,060
当年在戏班子结下的交情  终归还在的
to theatre folk like us, that means something.

310
00:19:40,010 --> 00:19:42,750
是啊  我也这么想
Yes, I'm sure it does.

311
00:20:12,050 --> 00:20:13,370
谢谢  女士  谢谢
Thank you, Madam. Thank you.

312
00:20:14,670 --> 00:20:16,090
这么贴心
This is very lovely.

313
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,960
你这会儿不该在办公室吗
Shouldn't you be at the office?

314
00:20:17,970 --> 00:20:19,850
罗斯孟德姑妈都派车来了
Aunt Rosamund's sending her car.

315
00:20:19,850 --> 00:20:21,250
我很想你
I've missed you.

316
00:20:21,620 --> 00:20:23,730
每时每刻  我都在想你
I haven't stopped thinking about you for one moment.

317
00:20:23,730 --> 00:20:24,990
我不是来了吗
Well, I'm here now.

318
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:28,280
我听到了一些消息  让我非常激动
I couldn't be more thrilled because I've got some news...

319
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:30,920
也算不上消息  算是个想法吧
Well, not news, more an idea.

320
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:32,070
说来听听
Go on.

321
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:33,420
我研究了一下
I've done some research,

322
00:20:33,420 --> 00:20:35,970
发现并非所有国家都如英格兰一般
and discovered not every country is the same as England.

323
00:20:35,970 --> 00:20:37,120
真是大发现啊
You amaze me.

324
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:38,620
不  我是说在其他国家
No, I mean there are places

325
00:20:38,620 --> 00:20:40,670
精神失常可以作为离婚的理由
where lunacy is grounds for divorce,

326
00:20:40,670 --> 00:20:44,500
像在葡萄牙  希腊  还有德国
Portugal and Greece and even Germany.

327
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:46,850
但是  那得是当地居民才行吧
But, wouldn't you have to live there?

328
00:20:46,850 --> 00:20:49,250
不  不  我只是粗浅地了解了一下
No, no, I'm just finding out what's involved.

329
00:20:49,620 --> 00:20:53,240
但如果我真的移民德国  你会和我一起去吗
But if I did live in Germany, would you come with me?

330
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:57,230
你好  伯恩斯
Oh. Hello, Burns.

331
00:20:57,710 --> 00:21:00,100
这位是伯恩斯  罗斯孟德姑妈的司机
This is Burns, Aunt Rosamund's chauffeur.

332
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:01,860
下午好  小姐
Good afternoon, m'lady.

333
00:21:05,020 --> 00:21:05,930
需要载你一程吗
Can I give you a lift?

334
00:21:05,930 --> 00:21:08,870
不了  我坐出租就好  方向不同
No, I'll take a taxi. It's the opposite direction.

335
00:21:08,980 --> 00:21:10,380
那晚上见
I'll see you tonight.

336
00:21:16,940 --> 00:21:19,260
是我来得太早了吗
Oh. Am I too early?

337
00:21:19,260 --> 00:21:21,350
不是  是下午茶上晚了
No. I'm afraid tea was a little late.

338
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:24,600
天呐  你能应付得来吗  要不要我帮忙
Oh, dear. Can you manage? Should I give you a hand?

339
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:26,820
我能行  谢谢  维斯特小姐
I can manage, thank you, Miss West.

340
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:28,650
快来  小宝贝
Come to me, darling.

341
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:30,940
你好啊
Hello.

342
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:35,260
您的小王子来了  小姐
Now, here's the little Prince, m'lady.

343
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:41,280
您瞧他看到您有多高兴啊
See how happy he is to see his beautiful Mama?

344
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:42,640
上帝保佑他
God bless him.

345
00:21:43,660 --> 00:21:44,940
谢谢你  保姆
Thank you, Nanny.

346
00:21:47,670 --> 00:21:50,620
你说你失去了人生的目标
You say you have no purpose,

347
00:21:50,730 --> 00:21:52,580
可小乔治怎么办
but what about little George?

348
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:54,530
你肯定很关心他的
Surely you're interested in him?

349
00:21:54,530 --> 00:21:59,020
当然  但我不想多插手  让玛丽不悦
Of course, but I'm not going to drive Mary mad by interfering.

350
00:21:59,020 --> 00:22:02,270
做奶奶的就得插手
It's the job of grandmothers to interfere.

351
00:22:03,190 --> 00:22:05,690
是莫斯利来了
Oh, that's Molesley.

352
00:22:06,330 --> 00:22:08,910
他想见我  所以我们约好了时间
He asked to see me and I told him when he could come.

353
00:22:08,910 --> 00:22:11,150
是吗  我能留下吗
Oh? Well, may I stay?

354
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:14,060
还是你有秘密任务要安排
Or is it a secret assignation?

355
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:19,910
很抱歉打扰二位夫人了
Oh. I'm very sorry to interrupt your ladyship.

356
00:22:19,910 --> 00:22:21,450
找我什么事  莫斯利
What is it, Molesley?

357
00:22:22,870 --> 00:22:26,780
我想问问您  能否考虑让我重新回来工作
I came to ask if you'd consider giving me my old job back.

358
00:22:28,590 --> 00:22:32,390
不好意思  打扰你们谈私事了
I apologise for forcing myself on a private conversation.

359
00:22:32,390 --> 00:22:33,140
我这就走
I will go.

360
00:22:33,140 --> 00:22:35,980
请别走  夫人  没什么秘密可言
No please, m'lady. There's no mystery.

361
00:22:36,330 --> 00:22:41,380
因为那件事  我丢了工作
I've lost my job, because, well, for obvious reasons

362
00:22:41,890 --> 00:22:43,490
所以我想能不能回来工作
and I thought I'd ask here.

363
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:48,610
问题是  我并不需要管家
The trouble is, I have no need for a butler.

364
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:53,080
如今我只是个用托盘吃饭的老寡妇
These days I'm just an old widow who eats off a tray.

365
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:53,930
我明白
I see.

366
00:22:53,930 --> 00:22:55,780
不能因为自己是个老寡妇
Just because you're an old widow,

367
00:22:55,780 --> 00:22:58,330
就用托盘吃饭啊
I see no necessity to eat off a tray.

368
00:22:58,330 --> 00:22:59,990
我们俩可是不是同一种人
You and I are different.

369
00:23:00,350 --> 00:23:02,360
没错  这话不假
Yes, that is very true.

370
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:03,570
浪费您的时间了
I'm wasting your time.

371
00:23:03,570 --> 00:23:06,900
要是有空缺的职位
Should, should we hear of an opening...

372
00:23:07,380 --> 00:23:08,690
我们应该上哪找你呢
..where would we find you?

373
00:23:08,690 --> 00:23:11,110
我会搬去我父亲那儿  夫人
I'm moving to my father's house, m'lady.

374
00:23:35,140 --> 00:23:38,130
你有想过我对你说的话吗
Have you had any more time to think about what I said?

375
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:40,540
你是说我们罪恶地生活在一起
You mean our living in sin?

376
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:44,220
如果我离婚了  就不算罪恶了
We'd only live in sin as you call it, until the divorce.

377
00:23:45,130 --> 00:23:46,780
你不想跟我在一起吗
Don't you want to be with me?

378
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:51,370
你知道我想的  求之若渴
You know I do. More than anything.

379
00:23:57,090 --> 00:24:01,570
还有杜松子酒吗  先生  快喝完了
Erm, is there any more gin, sir? We're running rather low.

380
00:24:01,570 --> 00:24:04,070
好的  我...我去看看
Yes, I'll er, I'll have a look.

381
00:24:27,610 --> 00:24:29,620
上帝啊
Oh, my Lord!

382
00:24:36,190 --> 00:24:38,010
不胜荣幸  老夫人
This is an honour, your ladyship.

383
00:24:38,010 --> 00:24:39,830
我给你儿子捎个话
I have a message for your son.

384
00:24:40,150 --> 00:24:43,260
沙克尔顿夫人要来与我共进午宴
Lady Shackleton is joining me for luncheon.

385
00:24:43,260 --> 00:24:45,230
我想让他过来帮忙
I want him to come and help.

386
00:24:45,510 --> 00:24:47,360
那斯普拉特先生呢
But, what about Mr Spratt?

387
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:49,470
斯普拉特当然也在
Well, Spratt will be there, of course,

388
00:24:49,470 --> 00:24:52,980
但莫斯利还是可以帮忙嘛
but Molesley can still take an active part.

389
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:58,510
沙克尔顿夫人告诉我说她的管家要退休了
Lady Shackleton tells me her butler is retiring.

390
00:24:58,510 --> 00:25:00,740
那她不是要想办法另寻他人吗
Won't she have made arrangements to find another?

391
00:25:00,740 --> 00:25:02,320
关键就在这里
But that is the point.

392
00:25:02,390 --> 00:25:05,910
她还没有决定是否要找人接替他
She hasn't yet decided whether to replace him or not,

393
00:25:05,970 --> 00:25:09,950
所以要是莫斯利能够一展身手的话...
so if Molesley can demonstrate his skills...

394
00:25:10,630 --> 00:25:12,650
斯普拉特先生不介意吗
Mr Spratt won't mind?

395
00:25:12,650 --> 00:25:14,790
还轮不到他来介意
It is not his business to mind.

396
00:25:14,790 --> 00:25:16,600
那是当然  那么...
No. Well...

397
00:25:16,690 --> 00:25:19,400
好的  夫人  非常感谢
Very good, m'lady. Thank you very much.

398
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:31,720
我已经把那封信揉成一团扔掉了
You took a letter out of my waste paper basket

399
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:34,650
你竟然还把它从我的废纸篓里捡了出来
when I had clearly crumpled it and thrown it away?

400
00:25:34,650 --> 00:25:36,020
我知道你不开心了
I could see it had upset you.

401
00:25:36,020 --> 00:25:37,040
我想知道为什么
I wanted to know why.

402
00:25:37,040 --> 00:25:38,440
那是自然
I'm sure.

403
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:39,660
但你有没有想过
But it didn't occur to you

404
00:25:39,660 --> 00:25:42,820
你或许不该操心我为什么不开心
it might not be your concern WHY I was upset?

405
00:25:42,820 --> 00:25:44,520
不管怎样  我操了心  读了信
Well, anyway, I did it and I read it

406
00:25:44,520 --> 00:25:45,910
我还去见了他
and I went to see him!

407
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:49,850
你难道不想知道他境况如何吗
Don't you want to know how he is?

408
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:54,040
我要是想知道的话  我就回信给他了
If I wanted to know how he is, I would have answered his letter.

409
00:25:54,170 --> 00:25:57,020
卡森先生  他在济贫院里
Mr Carson, he's in the workhouse!

410
00:25:59,390 --> 00:26:01,740
如果你想知道
And in case you're wondering,

411
00:26:01,980 --> 00:26:05,900
那里就跟狄更斯的小说里描述的一样糟糕
it's as bad as if we were reading about it in a novel by Dickens.

412
00:26:06,330 --> 00:26:08,380
济贫院不是应该都已经关闭了吗
Haven't they closed the workhouses?

413
00:26:08,380 --> 00:26:11,270
没有  还留下来了一些
No. They haven't. Not all of them.

414
00:26:12,230 --> 00:26:15,370
起码雨淋不着他
Well, at least he's in the dry.

415
00:26:15,540 --> 00:26:16,730
雨倒是淋不着他
If you can call it dry

416
00:26:16,730 --> 00:26:20,110
可是那里的每一寸空气都弥漫着霉味
when there's mould in the very air you breathe.

417
00:26:20,110 --> 00:26:23,540
这个男人曾经跟你一起唱歌跳舞
This is a man you sang and danced with.

418
00:26:23,590 --> 00:26:25,230
你真的无动于衷吗
Do you feel nothing?

419
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:28,680
我想我帮不上忙
I don't feel I could be helpful, no.

420
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:31,130
而且那是我想要忘掉的一段时光
And I would thank you not to remind me

421
00:26:31,130 --> 00:26:34,380
我希望你不要再提
of a time in my life I prefer to forget.

422
00:26:36,550 --> 00:26:38,310
可我们为什么需要这个
But why would we need it?

423
00:26:38,310 --> 00:26:41,800
这是个搅拌机  可以打蛋  搅奶油什么的
It's a mixer. It beats eggs and whips cream and all sorts.

424
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,190
可那是你跟艾薇的活儿
But you and Ivy do that!

425
00:26:43,190 --> 00:26:45,310
我们可巴不得不干那活儿呢
And we'd be glad not to, thank you very much.

426
00:26:45,310 --> 00:26:46,930
伊迪丝小姐有没有说为什么买这个
Did Lady Edith say why she got it?

427
00:26:47,260 --> 00:26:48,600
夫人让她买的
Her ladyship asked her to.

428
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:50,720
她想让我们省点力气
She wants to save us a bit of elbow grease.

429
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:52,830
你们两个傻丫头
You don't understand!

430
00:26:52,980 --> 00:26:54,250
要不了多久
Before too long,

431
00:26:54,250 --> 00:26:58,050
夫人就可以随便找个村妇来管厨房了
her ladyship could run the kitchen with a woman from the village.

432
00:26:58,230 --> 00:27:00,010
这些面包机啊
What with these toasters and

433
00:27:00,010 --> 00:27:02,430
搅拌机啊什么的  要害我们失业了
mixers and such like, we'd be out of a job.

434
00:27:02,430 --> 00:27:06,370
-我想试试嘛  -那随你的便
- I want to try it. - Then on your own head be it!

435
00:27:07,850 --> 00:27:10,130
你喜欢你的卡片吗  艾薇
Did you like your card, Ivy?

436
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:11,050
关你什么事
What's it to you?

437
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:12,390
这还不明显
That'd be telling.

438
00:27:12,390 --> 00:27:14,020
别听他的  他在逗你呢
Don't listen. He's just teasing.

439
00:27:14,020 --> 00:27:18,150
好啦  你们俩走开  该干活了
Come on. Clear out, you two. There's work to be done.

440
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:21,130
你觉得是不是吉米寄的卡片
Do you think that means that Jimmy sent it?

441
00:27:21,130 --> 00:27:23,310
没准他只是觉得逗我们很好玩吧
Maybe he thinks it fun to tease.

442
00:27:23,570 --> 00:27:24,730
但是  你想过没有
But, don't you see?

443
00:27:25,030 --> 00:27:28,220
如果我的是吉米寄的  那你的是谁寄的
If Jimmy sent mine, then who sent yours?

444
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:37,220
-托马斯  -你该叫巴罗先生
- Thomas? - Mr Barrow to you.

445
00:27:37,220 --> 00:27:38,940
你能不能跟帕特莫太太说一声
Can you tell Mrs Patmore

446
00:27:38,940 --> 00:27:41,310
茜玻小姐的茶点不要炒蛋
I won't want the scrambled egg for Miss Sybbie's tea.

447
00:27:41,310 --> 00:27:43,350
你从这里走  下楼梯
If you go through here and down the stairs,

448
00:27:43,350 --> 00:27:44,630
就能自己跟她说了
you can tell her yourself.

449
00:27:44,630 --> 00:27:46,690
拜托帮个忙  我忙的不可开交
Do it. Please. I can't stop.

450
00:27:46,690 --> 00:27:48,610
孩子们没人看呢
The children are on their own.

451
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:51,310
既然罗斯打算去找人
Why did I struggle across

452
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:53,590
我去伦敦跑腿做什么
London if Rose was going to sort it out?

453
00:27:53,590 --> 00:27:55,510
你还有别的事情要做
You had other things to do.

454
00:27:56,050 --> 00:27:59,330
那也不是罗斯在邮局窗口放广告卡的理由
It doesn't explain why rose put the card in the Post Office window.

455
00:27:59,330 --> 00:28:01,240
我只是觉得如果能找个当地人
I just thought how much quicker

456
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:03,530
那大概会快得多
it would be if we could find someone local.

457
00:28:03,710 --> 00:28:05,070
我觉得我有责任这么做
I do feel responsible.

458
00:28:05,070 --> 00:28:06,580
你收到任何回复了吗
Have you had any answers yet?

459
00:28:06,580 --> 00:28:08,530
我们收到了三个  其中一个很不错
We've had three and one's promising,

460
00:28:08,530 --> 00:28:10,690
我们会在周五去里彭见她
so we'll see her in Ripon on Friday.

461
00:28:10,750 --> 00:28:12,430
为什么她不来这里
Why isn't she coming here?

462
00:28:12,650 --> 00:28:15,190
她要照顾姨妈  走不开
She's looking after her aunt, she can't get away.

463
00:28:15,190 --> 00:28:17,090
你该回到我们身边来了
It's time for you to come back to us.

464
00:28:17,420 --> 00:28:19,000
你有什么建议
What would you suggest?

465
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:22,420
找点感兴趣的事情  不管什么事
Take an interest in something, doesn't matter what.

466
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:26,330
诗歌...或者木艺
Poetry...or carpentry.

467
00:28:26,970 --> 00:28:30,300
-历史或者帽子  -我对乔治感兴趣
- History or hats. - I'm interested in George.

468
00:28:31,070 --> 00:28:32,380
是吗
Are you?

469
00:28:32,580 --> 00:28:34,040
我会的
I will be.

470
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:37,870
你今天都干了些什么
What have you been doing today?

471
00:28:38,170 --> 00:28:41,170
就是修理车间的各种事情
Well, it's this whole business with the repair shop.

472
00:28:41,170 --> 00:28:44,240
汤姆  别拿那些无聊的事情烦她
Tom, don't bore her with all that nonsense.

473
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:46,830
-是我的错  我先问他的  -即便如此
- It's my fault. I asked. - Even so.

474
00:28:46,900 --> 00:28:48,820
你要做的就是开心起来
You concentrate on feeling better.

475
00:28:48,820 --> 00:28:50,930
你不必为其他任何事操心
You mustn't worry about anything else.

476
00:28:57,060 --> 00:28:59,380
你寄了情人节贺卡吗
Did you send a Valentine's card?

477
00:28:59,380 --> 00:29:00,340
或许吧
Suppose I did.

478
00:29:00,340 --> 00:29:02,720
-是给艾薇的吗  -这不管你的事
- Was it to Ivy? - That's my business.

479
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:04,890
你不会真给艾薇寄了卡片吧
You didn't really send Ivy a card?

480
00:29:04,890 --> 00:29:06,380
有可能吗
Is it likely?

481
00:29:06,900 --> 00:29:08,790
我给安斯特拉瑟老夫人寄了一张
I sent one to Lady Anstruther.

482
00:29:08,870 --> 00:29:09,650
我之前在她那儿工作
I used to worked for her

483
00:29:09,650 --> 00:29:11,080
听说她要从法国回来了
and I heard she's coming back from France.

484
00:29:11,080 --> 00:29:12,560
或许能用上她
She might be useful.

485
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,010
你这样会不会太唐突了
Wasn't that a bit forward?

486
00:29:15,010 --> 00:29:16,560
我觉得她不会介意的
Oh, I don't think she'll mind.

487
00:29:18,130 --> 00:29:20,090
说实话  休斯太太
To be honest, Mrs Hughes,

488
00:29:20,590 --> 00:29:23,000
我认为这事与我毫无关系
I don't see that it's any of my business.

489
00:29:23,910 --> 00:29:26,960
真没料到您会说出这种话  夫人
That's something I never thought I'd hear you say, ma'am.

490
00:29:27,950 --> 00:29:30,560
一个在济贫院的可怜人 
A wretched man is in the workhouse

491
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:32,480
他向我们求助
and he reaches out to us for rescue.

492
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:34,480
他是向卡森求助
Well, he reached out to Carson.

493
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:36,500
我不知道你想让我做什么
I don't see what you want me to do.

494
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:38,280
卡劳利夫人  我
Mrs Crawley, I...

495
00:29:38,870 --> 00:29:41,060
我在想能否把他带到这来
I wondered if I could bring him here.

496
00:29:41,450 --> 00:29:42,770
这里
Here?

497
00:29:42,770 --> 00:29:45,770
如果我俩能向当局替他作担保
If you and I were to vouch for him to the authorities,

498
00:29:45,770 --> 00:29:48,180
就一定能把他从那地方弄出来
I'm sure we could get him away from that place.

499
00:29:48,180 --> 00:29:50,410
可为什么带到这儿来  为什么不是唐顿
But why here? Why not the Abbey?

500
00:29:50,410 --> 00:29:52,930
照顾他不该是卡森的责任吗
Isn't he Carson's responsibility?

501
00:29:52,930 --> 00:29:54,970
可遗憾的是
I'm sorry to say it, but,

502
00:29:55,070 --> 00:29:58,250
卡森先生已经对他的老伙计弃之不顾了
Mr Carson has turned his back on his old pal.

503
00:29:58,380 --> 00:29:59,660
我明白了
I see.

504
00:29:59,870 --> 00:30:04,580
所以即使会激怒卡森你也要把他救出来
So you want to risk Carson's wrath by rescuing this Mr Grigg?

505
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:08,950
他是个可怜的家伙  但还有工作的能力
He's a pitiful being, but he's not beyond work.

506
00:30:08,950 --> 00:30:12,560
如果他有机会还是能过上体面的生活的
He's not beyond a decent life, if he could find it.

507
00:30:14,650 --> 00:30:19,020
可依我现在的情况  恐怕无力...
You see, in my present state, I don't think I'm strong enough...

508
00:30:19,020 --> 00:30:20,770
您可以的  夫人
But you are, ma'am!

509
00:30:20,770 --> 00:30:23,550
只要您能化悲伤为力量
If you could just set aside your grief,

510
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:26,580
去帮助有需要的人
and use that strength for another's good.

511
00:30:34,560 --> 00:30:37,170
-布兰森先生  -卡森先生
- Mr Branson. - Mr Carson.

512
00:30:38,780 --> 00:30:40,710
我知道你不会认可
I know you won't think it correct,

513
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:43,820
但我有个难处得求你帮忙
but I need to ask your help in a difficult situation.

514
00:30:44,260 --> 00:30:45,430
求我帮忙  先生 
My help, sir?

515
00:30:45,430 --> 00:30:47,180
格兰瑟姆伯爵不同意我这么做
Lord Grantham is against me in this.

516
00:30:47,180 --> 00:30:49,630
马修走了  没人能帮我了
With Matthew gone, I've no-one else to turn to.

517
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:55,500
玛丽  玛丽小姐的情况丝毫没有好转
Mary, that is, Lady Mary, is not improving.

