00:40:46,950 --> 00:40:50,230
你面前有两个选择
you have a straightforward choice before you.

690
00:40:54,150 --> 00:40:55,840
你必须做出决定
You must choose...

691
00:40:57,200 --> 00:41:00,680
是消沉避世  或是积极生活
..Either death...or life.

692
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:03,760
您认为我该选择生活吗
And you think I should choose life?

693
00:41:15,580 --> 00:41:19,380
查理・格里格将住在卡劳利夫人那儿吗
Charlie Grigg is going to stay with Mrs Crawley?

694
00:41:19,380 --> 00:41:21,950
他被放出来了  卡劳利夫人监管他
The authorities have released him into her charge.

695
00:41:21,950 --> 00:41:24,070
我周五去接他
I'm collecting him on Friday.

696
00:41:24,250 --> 00:41:26,500
为什么她会同意呢
But why has she agreed to this?

697
00:41:26,500 --> 00:41:30,030
因为她很善良  他需要帮助
Because she is a kind woman, and he is a man in need.

698
00:41:30,030 --> 00:41:31,690
我不敢相信
I cannot believe you are

699
00:41:31,690 --> 00:41:34,860
你在这时候还打搅卡劳利夫人
imposing on Mrs Crawley at a time like this,

700
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:37,830
她经受着丧子之痛
when she is almost broken by grief.

701
00:41:38,430 --> 00:41:42,050
就是因为这样  我才要打搅她
It's BECAUSE of her grief I am imposing.

702
00:41:43,660 --> 00:41:46,340
-我不理解  -不
- I don't understand you. - No.

703
00:41:47,170 --> 00:41:48,670
你不能理解
You wouldn't.

704
00:41:49,850 --> 00:41:51,490
你得原谅玛丽
You must forgive Mary.

705
00:41:51,950 --> 00:41:53,410
我原谅她了
I do forgive her.

706
00:41:53,410 --> 00:41:55,650
她遍体鳞伤  我们得保护好她
She is broken and bruised and it is our job

707
00:41:55,650 --> 00:41:57,810
让她不再受伤害
to wrap her up and keep her safe from the world.

708
00:41:57,810 --> 00:41:59,680
不  罗伯特
No, Robert.

709
00:42:00,010 --> 00:42:03,100
我们要让她重新面对这个世界
It is our job to bring her back to the world.

710
00:42:03,100 --> 00:42:06,750
-我不这样认为  -真的吗
- I'm afraid that is not how I see it. - Really?

711
00:42:06,750 --> 00:42:08,410
那我只能说
Then I can only say that

712
00:42:08,410 --> 00:42:12,050
我可以不介意玛丽做的错误决定
while I will overlook Mary's poor judgement,

713
00:42:12,050 --> 00:42:15,120
但你就不应该了
I find it hard to overlook yours.

714
00:42:15,270 --> 00:42:16,610
晚安
Goodnight.

715
00:42:17,770 --> 00:42:21,420
伊迪丝  伊迪丝  周五一起吃饭吧
Oh, Edith, Edith, come to luncheon on Friday.

716
00:42:21,420 --> 00:42:23,320
-我...  -一定要来
- I... - I mean it.

717
00:42:23,450 --> 00:42:26,660
我需要你的帮助才能成功
I need your help to make things a success.

718
00:42:26,660 --> 00:42:28,350
为什么  我们要做什么
Why? What are we doing?

719
00:42:28,350 --> 00:42:31,630
我们要把莫斯利介绍给沙克尔顿夫人
We are selling Molesley to Lady Shackleton.

720
00:42:31,630 --> 00:42:33,340
是介绍他去做仆人
You mean as a servant?

721
00:42:34,510 --> 00:42:38,230
不  介绍他去洗衣服  
No. As a Chinese laundryman

722
00:42:44,910 --> 00:42:47,610
幸好你是一个人  你得帮我
Thank God you're alone. You've got to help me.

723
00:42:48,150 --> 00:42:49,450
你们俩怎么了
What's the matter with you two?

724
00:42:49,450 --> 00:42:52,130
不知道  我跟着他去看看吧
I don't know, but I'd better go with him if I want to find out.

725
00:42:57,030 --> 00:42:59,390
天啊  你怎么了
Oh, my Lord, what have you done?

726
00:42:59,620 --> 00:43:00,940
她在酒吧喝高了
She got a bit tiddly down the pub.

727
00:43:00,940 --> 00:43:04,580
-她不是喝高了  她都醉了  -他一直买酒
- She's not tiddly. She's drunk! - He kept buying them.

728
00:43:04,580 --> 00:43:06,530
-你想做什么  -我没想做什么
- What were you trying to do? - Nothing.

729
00:43:07,130 --> 00:43:08,370
她只是很少喝酒
She's just not used to it.

730
00:43:08,370 --> 00:43:09,590
走吧
Come on.

731
00:43:12,990 --> 00:43:14,880
-怎么回事  -艾薇不舒服
- What on earth?! - Ivy's not very well.

732
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:18,150
岂止是不舒服啊  快扶她进来
That's the understatement of the year. Bring her inside.

733
00:43:27,330 --> 00:43:30,970
-帕特莫太太睡了吗  -应该睡了  谢天谢地 	
- Has Mrs Patmore gone to bed? - She must have, thank goodness.

734
00:43:30,970 --> 00:43:33,330
-你想做什么  -我没想做什么
- What were you trying to do? - I wasn't trying to do anything.

735
00:43:33,330 --> 00:43:34,950
最好是这样
As long as you weren't.

736
00:43:37,180 --> 00:43:38,380
来擦脸
Here.

737
00:43:42,840 --> 00:43:45,480
-感觉怎样  -好点了  谢谢
- How are you feeling? - A bit better, thank you.

738
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:47,070
你差点闯大祸了
You could have done real damage.

739
00:43:47,070 --> 00:43:50,270
-跟我来  -贝茨先生怎么办
- You come along with me now. - What about Mr Bates?

740
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:52,060
他不会找你吗
Won't he be missing you?

741
00:43:52,380 --> 00:43:55,480
贝茨先生得等着了
Mr Bates must wait his turn.

742
00:43:55,480 --> 00:43:57,480
我真不是存心的  艾薇  
Meant no harm, Ivy, honest.

743
00:43:58,050 --> 00:43:59,920
你不会把这事说出去吧
You won't say anything about this, will you?

744
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:01,210
当然不会
'Course not.

745
00:44:01,250 --> 00:44:02,380
来吧
Come on.

746
00:44:03,110 --> 00:44:04,630
我不是故意的
It wasn't deliberate, you know.

747
00:44:05,730 --> 00:44:08,530
我知道你假装喜欢她来让我难堪
I know you only pretend to like her to tease me.

748
00:44:09,970 --> 00:44:12,260
为什么你不告诉她  那张卡不是你寄的
Why don't you tell her you didn't send that card?

749
00:44:19,740 --> 00:44:23,340
早安  卡劳利夫人  我不知道您来了
Oh good morning, Mrs Crawley. I didn't know you were here.

750
00:44:23,880 --> 00:44:25,250
阿尔弗雷德让我进来的
Alfred let me in.

751
00:44:26,200 --> 00:44:28,390
我来见我孙子
I wanted to see Master George,

752
00:44:29,060 --> 00:44:33,220
不过维斯特保姆觉得现在不合适
but I'm afraid...Nanny West didn't think it a good time.

753
00:44:33,790 --> 00:44:35,700
卡劳利夫人
Oh, er, Mrs Crawley...

754
00:44:36,050 --> 00:44:39,380
我听说您要收留格里格先生
I understand you are offering shelter to Mr Grigg.

755
00:44:39,590 --> 00:44:41,280
对  他今天下午就到
Yes. He's arriving this afternoon.

756
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:43,130
只是  我不希望您是为了我
Only I should hate to feel you were doing this

757
00:44:43,130 --> 00:44:45,140
才这么做的
out of consideration for me.

758
00:44:45,140 --> 00:44:48,400
格里格先生完全能处理好自己的事情
Mr Grigg is perfectly capable of managing his own affairs.

759
00:44:48,400 --> 00:44:51,290
可他都落魄到救济院了
Not very successfully if he ends up in a workhouse.

760
00:44:51,290 --> 00:44:54,970
我只是不希望您把精力和善心浪费在
I just don't want you to waste your energy and kindness

761
00:44:54,970 --> 00:44:57,280
不值得的人身上
on an unworthy recipient.

762
00:44:57,290 --> 00:44:59,310
起码不是这种时候
Not at such a time.

763
00:44:59,310 --> 00:45:00,800
我懂
I understand.

764
00:45:01,810 --> 00:45:03,460
不过  卡森
But you see, Carson,

765
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:07,440
我差点要忘记自己还有精力和善心了
I'd almost forgotten I had either energy or kindness in me.

766
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:11,170
这不是很让人欣慰吗
So that's something, isn't it?

767
00:45:16,360 --> 00:45:19,350
-她为什么要去里彭见她  -不知道
- Why is she seeing her in Ripon? - I don't know.

768
00:45:19,350 --> 00:45:21,670
夫人不等广告结果了吗
Her ladyship won't wait for the advertisement?

769
00:45:21,670 --> 00:45:23,080
要是这位不合格  她会继续等  
She will if this one's no good,

770
00:45:23,080 --> 00:45:25,130
但她想赶快办妥
but she wants to get on with it.

771
00:45:27,320 --> 00:45:28,700
你感觉怎么样了  艾薇
How are you, Ivy?

772
00:45:29,690 --> 00:45:31,250
不太好
Not wonderful.

773
00:45:37,320 --> 00:45:39,300
谁都有年轻的时候
I suppose we were all young once.

774
00:45:39,300 --> 00:45:42,230
对  不过你永葆青春
Yes, but you stayed young.

775
00:45:42,590 --> 00:45:44,010
这点跟别人不一样
That's the difference.

776
00:45:46,850 --> 00:45:47,900
不好意思  布雷思韦特小姐
Forgive me, Miss Braithwaite,

777
00:45:47,900 --> 00:45:51,160
我总觉得自己以前见过你
but I have the strangest feeling I've seen you before.

778
00:45:51,160 --> 00:45:53,740
是的  我正准备提这件事
Well, yes. I was just coming to that.

779
00:45:53,740 --> 00:45:57,860
我曾经在唐顿庄园做过工  不过时间很短
You see, I worked at Downton Abbey, but only for a short time.

780
00:45:57,860 --> 00:45:58,750
为什么呢
Why was that?

781
00:45:58,750 --> 00:46:00,720
我当时做的是女仆  夫人
I was a housemaid then, m'lady,

782
00:46:00,720 --> 00:46:03,120
我觉得该做点更有难度的工作
and I was starting to feel it was time to move on.

783
00:46:03,120 --> 00:46:04,340
是这样啊
I see.

784
00:46:04,340 --> 00:46:07,680
我报名上了美发课  我还会做针线活
So, I took a course in hairdressing, and I could always sew.

785
00:46:07,680 --> 00:46:09,650
后来你做了贴身女仆
And you got a job as a lady's maid.

786
00:46:09,660 --> 00:46:13,190
是的  夫人  但只做了几个月
I did, m'lady, but it only lasted for a few months

787
00:46:13,190 --> 00:46:15,700
因为我侍奉的老夫人去世了
because the old lady I was working for died.

788
00:46:15,700 --> 00:46:17,430
真遗憾
I am sorry.

789
00:46:17,950 --> 00:46:20,750
我知道自己的资历不深  夫人
I know I don't sound very experienced, m'lady,

790
00:46:21,040 --> 00:46:25,270
但我很勤快  而且我还练过手了
but I'm a very hard worker and I've practised what I've learned.

791
00:46:25,380 --> 00:46:28,870
要是你之前在唐顿做过工的话
Well, I shall obviously have to talk to Mrs Hughes

792
00:46:28,870 --> 00:46:30,710
我得问一下休斯太太
if you've worked for us before.

793
00:46:30,710 --> 00:46:34,430
我走的时候  她还给我写了封很不错的推荐信呢
She gave me a wonderful reference. When I left.

794
00:46:34,430 --> 00:46:36,720
这点确实很有说服力
That does seem very encouraging.

795
00:46:36,720 --> 00:46:39,200
快答应吧  柯拉堂亲
Please say yes, Cousin Cora.

796
00:46:41,430 --> 00:46:43,100
你真的想做这份工作吗
You definitely want the position?

797
00:46:43,100 --> 00:46:46,930
是的  夫人  我很喜欢唐顿这个地方
Oh, I do, m'lady. I enjoyed Downton ever so much.

798
00:46:46,930 --> 00:46:49,490
我当时只是觉得那份工作没太有挑战性
It was just that the work wasn't sufficiently demanding.

799
00:46:49,490 --> 00:46:51,610
你什么时候能上岗
When would you be able to start?

800
00:46:52,300 --> 00:46:54,310
听您吩咐  夫人
Whenever you want me, your ladyship.

801
00:46:54,310 --> 00:46:57,670
-你能安排好你姨妈的事吗  -我姨妈
- You can make arrangements for your aunt? - My aunt?

802
00:46:58,570 --> 00:46:59,570
你不就是因为要照顾她
I thought that was why you couldn't

803
00:46:59,570 --> 00:47:00,940
才不能去唐顿面试吗
come to Downton for the interview.

804
00:47:00,940 --> 00:47:02,660
抱歉  是这样的  
I'm sorry. Of course it was.

805
00:47:02,660 --> 00:47:04,720
我能得到这份工作都有点晕头了
I'm quite dizzy I've got the job.

806
00:47:04,720 --> 00:47:07,180
我能安排好我姨妈的事
Erm, yes, I can make arrangements for my aunt.

807
00:47:07,180 --> 00:47:09,080
您用不着担心
Don't worry about that.

808
00:47:09,080 --> 00:47:10,980
那就这么定了
It's settled, then.

809
00:47:17,180 --> 00:47:20,390
我一个人完全可以为三位夫人侍奉午餐
I'm perfectly capable of serving luncheon to three ladies.

810
00:47:20,390 --> 00:47:21,990
你来做什么
So, why are you here?

811
00:47:22,490 --> 00:47:26,740
我觉得她想把我介绍给沙克尔顿夫人
I've an idea that she wants to introduce me to Lady Shackleton.

812
00:47:28,560 --> 00:47:30,730
这不是你自己的主意吗
Are you sure this isn't your idea?

813
00:47:32,550 --> 00:47:34,830
是不是你让老夫人为你做引荐
I wonder if you haven't pushed her ladyship into it,

814
00:47:34,830 --> 00:47:37,620
这样你就可以在她面前出风头了
so you could just show off in front of her.

815
00:47:37,620 --> 00:47:39,210
当然不是
Certainly not!

816
00:47:39,640 --> 00:47:41,630
我觉得你想抢我的位置
I think it's my job you're after!

817
00:47:42,630 --> 00:47:45,540
-这根本就与沙克尔顿夫人无关  -才不是呢
- Nothing to do with Lady Shackleton. - No!

818
00:47:45,780 --> 00:47:47,200
我凭什么信你
So you say.

819
00:47:51,770 --> 00:47:54,070
我要去宣布开饭了
Well, I'm going to announce luncheon.

820
00:47:58,900 --> 00:48:02,160
我警告你  别打其他主意了
But I'm warning you. That's all.

821
00:48:09,540 --> 00:48:12,720
我儿子告诉我  撤销农产品补贴的决定
My son tells me that this decision to remove the farm subsidies

822
00:48:12,720 --> 00:48:16,640
对全国上下的地产打击非常大
has dealt a terrible blow to landed estates up and down the country.

823
00:48:16,640 --> 00:48:19,080
那个劳合・乔治先生太过分了
That awful Mr Lloyd George.

824
00:48:19,150 --> 00:48:20,350
我也这么觉得
I agree.

825
00:48:20,790 --> 00:48:23,690
我时常怀疑他是不是德国人
You know, I sometimes wonder if he isn't really German,

826
00:48:23,690 --> 00:48:26,110
只是假装成威尔士人而已
just pretending to be Welsh.

827
00:48:28,320 --> 00:48:31,480
见到你真高兴  莫斯利
It's nice to see you here, Molesley.

828
00:48:31,890 --> 00:48:35,510
莫斯利一直都在勤勤恳恳地扶持这个家
Molesley's always been a great supporter of the family.

829
00:48:35,510 --> 00:48:36,720
真好
That's good to hear.

830
00:48:36,720 --> 00:48:39,330
是啊  我和奶奶经常说
Oh, yes, Granny and I are always saying

831
00:48:39,330 --> 00:48:42,240
-莫斯利最可靠了  -没人比得上他
- there's no-one more reliable than Molesley. - No-one.

832
00:48:42,240 --> 00:48:43,760
小心点  莫斯利先生
Careful, Mr Molesley!

833
00:48:44,520 --> 00:48:46,970
你没事吧  莫斯利
Oh? Are you quite well, Molesley?

834
00:48:46,970 --> 00:48:48,230
没事  老夫人
Yes, your ladyship.

835
00:48:50,260 --> 00:48:53,680
你在伦敦做什么  伊迪斯
What are you doing in London, Edith dear?

836
00:48:53,680 --> 00:48:55,820
就是见一些人
Oh you know, seeing people.

837
00:48:55,820 --> 00:48:58,220
你用不着大喊大叫吧  我又没做错什么
There's no need to shout! I wasn't doing anything wrong.

838
00:48:58,220 --> 00:49:01,080
我还以为你要失手掉到地上了
It looked to me as if you were about to drop it.

839
00:49:01,080 --> 00:49:03,310
-我没有  -那就好
- Well, I wasn't. - Very well.

840
00:49:03,480 --> 00:49:05,920
给  上这道菜
Here, take this.

841
00:49:08,620 --> 00:49:09,850
莫斯利  你怎么了
Molesley?

842
00:49:10,270 --> 00:49:11,110
对不起  老夫人
I'm sorry, m'lady.

843
00:49:11,110 --> 00:49:14,360
我不知道这个盘子这么烫
I didn't realise the plate was so hot.

844
00:49:14,880 --> 00:49:17,210
可怜人  他似乎没怎么做过这些呢
Poor man. He seems quite new to this kind of work.

845
00:49:17,210 --> 00:49:18,280
是吗
Does he?

846
00:49:19,040 --> 00:49:23,290
不不  不是这样的  这正是莫斯利的优点
Oh, but that is, no dear no, that is Molesley's strength.

847
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:26,540
他总是愿意迎接挑战
You see he is always ready for a challenge.

848
00:49:26,540 --> 00:49:29,830
那您允许他做这样的尝试真是太好心了
I think it was very kind of you to allow him to have a go at it.

849
00:49:30,520 --> 00:49:33,070
嗯  我们也是尽力而为嘛
Yes well, we, we try to do our best.

850
00:49:33,070 --> 00:49:35,930
如今有很多人不得不做一些
I do find it very hard these days to see how many men

851
00:49:35,930 --> 00:49:39,360
他们力所不能及的事  真是难为他们了
are forced to take employment for which they are quite unsuited.

852
00:49:39,480 --> 00:49:43,620
希望你能尽快回去做你的本职
I hope you'll soon get back to whatever it is you're trained for.

853
00:50:14,440 --> 00:50:18,180
来吧  格里格先生  休斯太太把你的事都告诉我了
Come in, Mr Grigg. Mrs Hughes has told me all about you.

854
00:50:18,180 --> 00:50:19,910
谢谢您  卡劳利夫人
Thank you, Mrs Crawley.

855
00:50:23,580 --> 00:50:27,750
查理来没来啊
I was er... I was wondering if Charlie might be here.

856
00:50:28,120 --> 00:50:31,300
-查理・卡森  -没有  卡森先生很忙
- Charlie Carson. - No. Mr Carson's very busy.

857
00:50:31,300 --> 00:50:34,020
但我会转告他你安全到达了
But, I'll tell him that you've arrived safely.

858
00:50:34,020 --> 00:50:35,980
但他知道我要来吧
But, he does know I'm coming here?

859
00:50:36,550 --> 00:50:38,080
我们昨天谈过了
We talked of it yesterday.

860
00:50:38,350 --> 00:50:39,890
我给你放了洗澡水
Now, I've run a bath

861
00:50:39,900 --> 00:50:42,610
还在教堂找到了些募捐的干净衣物
and dug out some clean clothes from the missionary barrel.

862
00:50:42,610 --> 00:50:45,330
应该会合身  回头再去弄些更好的衣服来
They should fit you, at least until we can find something better.

863
00:50:45,330 --> 00:50:46,390
这边走  格里格先生
This way, Mr. Grigg.

864
00:50:46,390 --> 00:50:50,200
-您太好了  -哪里的话  这不算什么
- You're very kind. - Nonsense. It's the least I can do.

865
00:50:54,780 --> 00:50:55,840
我去安排他住下
While I'm sorting him out,

866
00:50:55,840 --> 00:50:57,550
你去一趟厨房
I wondered if you'd look in at the kitchen

867
00:50:57,550 --> 00:50:59,250
告诉菲尔德太太他来了
and tell Mrs Field he's arrived

868
00:50:59,250 --> 00:51:01,220
拿托盘把午餐端给他  好吗
and to put his luncheon on a tray.

869
00:51:01,540 --> 00:51:03,200
我觉得他今天该卧床休息
I think he should stay in bed today

870
00:51:03,200 --> 00:51:05,270
然后再做打算
and then we can see where we are.

871
00:51:05,510 --> 00:51:08,070
他说得对  您真是好心
He's right. You're very kind.

872
00:51:08,170 --> 00:51:11,840
不不  我们都得尽力而为嘛
No, no. We must all do what we can.

873
00:51:39,520 --> 00:51:40,590
你好啊
Hello.

874
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:43,520
你可...真美
You look...very glamorous.

875
00:51:43,640 --> 00:51:45,900
我觉得我该好好打扮一下
I thought I'd make a bit of an effort.

876
00:51:46,260 --> 00:51:47,430
真是太好了
I'm glad you did.

877
00:51:48,600 --> 00:51:50,040
我点了些酒
I've ordered some wine for us.

878
00:51:50,740 --> 00:51:52,840
天呐  真奢侈呢
Heavens, how spoiling.

879
00:51:56,220 --> 00:51:57,820
我很喜欢这里
I love the Criterion.

880
00:52:03,530 --> 00:52:05,040
感觉好疯狂
It feels so wild.

881
00:52:05,660 --> 00:52:06,960
跟一个男人出来私会
To be out with a man,

882
00:52:07,180 --> 00:52:10,150
在伦敦的奢华饭店吃饭喝酒
drinking and dining in a smart London restaurant.

883
00:52:10,560 --> 00:52:12,990
别说十年前  就是五年前  你能想象
Can you imagine being allowed to do anything of the sort

884
00:52:12,990 --> 00:52:15,090
做这样的事吗
five years ago, never mind ten?

885
00:52:15,090 --> 00:52:16,740
战争改变了一切
The war changed everything.

886
00:52:17,120 --> 00:52:19,940
妈妈曾说我们绝不会在公共场所吃饭的
Mama used to say we could never eat anywhere public,

887
00:52:19,940 --> 00:52:22,190
除非是我们下榻的酒店
except an hotel we were staying in.

888
00:52:22,200 --> 00:52:25,410
她可能会带我们去丽兹酒店  但也就那样了
She might cheat and take us to the Ritz, but that was about it.

889
00:52:27,930 --> 00:52:29,290
我好爱你
I do love you so.

890
00:52:29,720 --> 00:52:30,570
是吗
Do you?

891
00:52:31,430 --> 00:52:32,760
那真好
I'm glad.

892
00:52:34,640 --> 00:52:36,210
我们就是为此庆祝吗
Is that what we're celebrating?

893
00:52:36,920 --> 00:52:39,040
对  还有我取得的进展
That, and my progress.

894
00:52:41,020 --> 00:52:45,190
我发现我可以在德国跟莉兹离婚
I've found out I can divorce Lizzie in Germany,

895
00:52:45,190 --> 00:52:47,900
前提是我成为德国公民
if I become a German citizen.

896
00:52:49,930 --> 00:52:54,130
你愿意为我成为德国人
You're willing to become a German citizen, for me?

897
00:52:54,540 --> 00:52:55,830
你真愿意这么做
You'd do that?

898
00:52:56,000 --> 00:52:58,510
如果我能娶你  我愿意成为爱斯基摩人
I'd become an Eskimo if it meant I could marry you.

899
00:52:58,700 --> 00:53:00,520
但是  德国
But...Germany?

900
00:53:02,030 --> 00:53:03,510
我们打了四年的仗
After four years of fighting,

901
00:53:03,520 --> 00:53:07,360
你愿意为我加入欧洲最令人仇视的民族吗
you'd join the most hated race in Europe for me?

902
00:53:14,630 --> 00:53:15,870
我能吻你吗
Can I kiss you?

903
00:53:16,300 --> 00:53:17,540
在这儿吗
What, here?

904
00:53:18,790 --> 00:53:22,300
-当着这么多人的面  -我不在乎
- In front of all these people? - I don't care.

905
00:53:23,090 --> 00:53:25,940
吻我吧
Kiss me. Now.

906
00:53:35,030 --> 00:53:37,430
艾德娜・布雷思韦特要回来了
Edna Braithwaite is coming back?

907
00:53:37,800 --> 00:53:40,010
我本想先跟你商量  但是
I would have talked it over with you first but...

908
00:53:40,210 --> 00:53:42,300
我看到你给她写了那么好的一份推荐信
When I saw that wonderful reference you wrote her.

909
00:53:42,300 --> 00:53:43,960
是  可那是因为
Yes, but that was because...

910
00:53:46,230 --> 00:53:48,190
我给她写了一份好推荐信
I wrote her a good reference

911
00:53:48,190 --> 00:53:50,690
因为我觉得她干活儿勤快利索
because I thought she was a good worker,

912
00:53:51,550 --> 00:53:53,920
但我不觉得她能当好贴身女仆
but I don't see her as a lady's maid.

913
00:53:55,720 --> 00:53:58,730
您不能等到收到广告回复之后
Couldn't you wait for the replies to the advertisement, m'lady,

914
00:53:58,730 --> 00:54:00,420
再做决定吗  夫人
before coming to a decision?

915
00:54:02,700 --> 00:54:04,820
真没想到  休斯太太
I'm surprised at you, Mrs Hughes.

916
00:54:08,560 --> 00:54:12,420
你真要阻止我帮助一个努力勤快的女孩吗
Do you want to prevent my giving a hard-working woman a helping hand?

917
00:54:20,680 --> 00:54:24,620
那张卡的确是吉米寄给艾薇的
You know, it WAS Jimmy sent that card to Ivy.

918
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:26,880
这你又不确定
You don't know that.

919
00:54:26,980 --> 00:54:28,140
我想没错
I think I do.

920
00:54:29,620 --> 00:54:32,850
可如果是他  那么我那张就是阿尔弗寄的
But, if it were him, then Alfie must have sent mine.

921
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:38,010
阿尔弗雷德  跟我来
Alfred. Come with me.

922
00:54:38,010 --> 00:54:40,730
-什么事  -你管呢  来就是了
- Why? - Never you mind. Just come along.

923
00:54:44,190 --> 00:54:45,520
莫斯利先生
Mr Molesley?

924
00:54:46,850 --> 00:54:47,800
你要来点什么吗
Can I get you anything?

925
00:54:47,810 --> 00:54:50,290
-来杯茶  -不不  不麻烦你了
- A cup of tea? - No. I don't want to be a bother.

926
00:54:50,300 --> 00:54:54,190
那顿午餐怎么样  伊迪丝小姐告诉我了
How was the famous luncheon? Lady Edith told me all about it.

927
00:54:54,500 --> 00:54:57,210
之前还是之后说的
Was that before or after?

928
00:54:57,210 --> 00:54:58,360
之前
Before.

929
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:01,320
那就这样吧  别再多说了
Right. Let's just leave it at that, shall we?

930
00:55:03,600 --> 00:55:05,290
休斯太太在找我
Mrs Hughes was looking for me.

931
00:55:05,300 --> 00:55:07,630
我看见她会休息室了  要我去叫她吗
I saw her go into her sitting room. Shall I fetch her?

932
00:55:07,630 --> 00:55:08,450
不必了
No need.

933
00:55:08,450 --> 00:55:11,040
很抱歉我之前没说
I'm sorry not to have mentioned it.

934
00:55:11,420 --> 00:55:13,180
是我给艾薇寄了卡片
I sent the card to Ivy.

935
00:55:14,450 --> 00:55:16,280
但是  吉米说
But...Jimmy said...

936
00:55:16,280 --> 00:55:17,620
他没寄
He didn't send one.

937
00:55:18,450 --> 00:55:21,270
如果他寄了  也没寄给唐顿的人
Or, if he did, it wasn't to anyone at Downton.

938
00:55:23,910 --> 00:55:25,390
晚安  帕特莫太太
Good night, Mrs Patmore.

939
00:55:33,430 --> 00:55:36,300
如果不是他  那是谁寄了卡片给我
If it weren't him, then who did send my card?

940
00:55:37,700 --> 00:55:39,120
我这下睡不着了
I won't sleep now.

941
00:55:39,120 --> 00:55:41,940
老天啊  是我寄的
Oh, for heaven's sake! I sent it.

942
00:55:42,530 --> 00:55:44,870
-你  -对
- You?! - Yes.

943
00:55:46,840 --> 00:55:49,700
我猜到阿尔弗雷德会给艾薇寄一张
I thought Alfred would buy one for Ivy,

944
00:55:50,020 --> 00:55:53,190
如果他寄了  我不希望你什么都没收到
and I didn't want you to have nothing to open if he did.

945
00:55:54,910 --> 00:55:56,520
如果我不该这么做  那很抱歉
I'm sorry if I did wrong.

946
00:55:56,900 --> 00:55:58,200
不  别这么说
No, don't be sorry.

947
00:55:59,540 --> 00:56:02,600
我虽然没有人暗恋  但至少有个好朋友
I may not have a follower, but at least I've got a friend.

948
00:56:04,500 --> 00:56:06,220
晚安  帕特莫太太
Goodnight, Mrs Patmore.

949
00:56:12,480 --> 00:56:13,910
我真不知道该怎么说
I didn't know what else to say.

950
00:56:13,910 --> 00:56:16,310
我的确给她写了份好推荐信
I had written her a good reference.

951
00:56:16,310 --> 00:56:17,800
但那是因为我求您
Only because I asked you to.

952
00:56:17,800 --> 00:56:20,440
那我该告诉夫人吗  布兰森先生
And was I to tell her that, Mr Branson,

953
00:56:20,470 --> 00:56:22,100
还有您提出要求的原因
and why you asked me?

954
00:56:22,110 --> 00:56:23,830
我去告诉她吧
It's up to me to tell her.

955
00:56:24,220 --> 00:56:25,800
是我搅起了这场麻烦
I'm the one who got us into this fix.

956
00:56:25,800 --> 00:56:26,860
不
No.

957
00:56:27,400 --> 00:56:30,030
夫人失去了一个女儿和一个女婿
Her ladyship has lost a daughter and a son-in-law.

958
00:56:30,030 --> 00:56:35,500
我不能让她觉得茜玻小姐的丈夫做了有失体面的事
I cannot now let her think that Lady Sybil's husband was unworthy.

959
00:56:35,550 --> 00:56:36,740
这对她会难以承受
It's too much.

960
00:56:38,300 --> 00:56:39,830
那我们怎么做
Then what are we to do?

961
00:56:40,410 --> 00:56:42,660
-不能留她在这儿  -不行也得行
- We can't have her here. - We must.

962
00:56:42,660 --> 00:56:43,500
我们让她回来
We'll let her come back

963
00:56:43,500 --> 00:56:46,350
并且保证她不会逾矩
and we'll make sure that she behaves herself.

964
00:56:46,700 --> 00:56:47,850
如果她不守规矩呢
And if she doesn't?

965
00:56:47,850 --> 00:56:50,150
我们得盯紧了她
We must keep a firm eye on her,

966
00:56:50,150 --> 00:56:51,900
希望我们可以指望你
and I hope we may rely on you

967
00:56:51,900 --> 00:56:54,350
确保艾德娜不会做什么出格的事
to see that Edna doesn't step out of line.

968
00:56:54,620 --> 00:56:55,690
当然
Of course.

969
00:56:56,100 --> 00:56:59,730
毕竟  她似乎的确接受了专业的训练
After all, she does appear to have acquired some proper training.

970
00:56:59,730 --> 00:57:01,410
这应该不假
I don't think that's a lie.

971
00:57:01,530 --> 00:57:05,330
或许她变得现实了
Maybe she's moved into the real world.

972
00:57:07,070 --> 00:57:10,680
我觉得就是颗定时炸弹
Well, it all sounds like a ticking bomb to me.

973
00:57:25,550 --> 00:57:29,160
好了  我的好宝贝
There, there, my precious boy,

974
00:57:29,160 --> 00:57:35,290
别让那司机的女儿再打扰你了
and don't let that chauffeur's daughter disturb you any more.

975
00:57:38,150 --> 00:57:40,240
给我睡觉
Go back to sleep,

976
00:57:40,240 --> 00:57:44,100
你个小杂种
you wicked little cross-breed.

977
00:57:46,890 --> 00:57:49,930
夫人  我没看见您
Your ladyship... I didn't see you there.

978
00:57:49,930 --> 00:57:51,760
显然如此
Obviously not.

979
00:57:52,020 --> 00:57:53,160
我就是...
I was just er...

980
00:57:53,160 --> 00:57:55,680
我就是跟茜玻小姐闹着玩呢
I was just having a game with Miss Sybbie.

981
00:57:55,680 --> 00:57:59,550
我要你今晚收拾东西  明天一早就走
I want you to pack tonight and leave first thing in the morning.

982
00:57:59,550 --> 00:58:00,650
但是  夫人
But, your ladyship...

983
00:58:00,650 --> 00:58:03,310
请把乔治少爷放回摇篮里
Please put Master George back into his crib.

984
00:58:03,910 --> 00:58:06,180
你不许再碰两个孩子了
You are not to touch the children again.

985
00:58:07,820 --> 00:58:09,980
我以为是维斯特保姆按的铃呢
Oh. I thought it was Nanny West ringing.

986
00:58:09,980 --> 00:58:13,740
不  休斯太太  维斯特保姆明早就会走了
No, Mrs Hughes, Nanny West is leaving in the morning.

987
00:58:13,830 --> 00:58:15,730
请你为她找张床  让她今晚过夜
Can you find her a bed for the night

988
00:58:15,730 --> 00:58:18,380
找一个女仆来陪孩子睡
and ask one of the maids to sleep with the children?

989
00:58:18,390 --> 00:58:20,550
但是  夫人  我就是说笑呢
But, your ladyship, I was only joking.

990
00:58:20,550 --> 00:58:22,610
我不想再说了
I prefer not to discuss it,

991
00:58:22,610 --> 00:58:23,480
除了告诉你
except to say that

992
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:26,520
你这样的观念在一个文明的家里待不下去
your values have no place in a civilised home!

993
00:58:28,080 --> 00:58:29,810
好了  休斯太太
Now, Mrs Hughes...

994
00:58:31,170 --> 00:58:33,840
维斯特保姆收拾东西的时候我就等在这儿
I'll wait here while Nanny West packs.

995
00:58:34,980 --> 00:58:37,860
你去找个女仆来  再收拾一间房
You will fetch a maid and prepare a room.

996
00:58:37,860 --> 00:58:41,410
要记住  不能让维斯特小姐跟孩子独处
You understand, Miss West is not to be left alone with the children.

997
00:58:41,410 --> 00:58:42,950
一分钟也不行
Not for one minute.

998
00:58:44,570 --> 00:58:45,980
不知道伊迪丝怎么样了
I wonder how Edith's getting on.

999
00:58:45,980 --> 00:58:48,000
她去伦敦去得很频啊
She has quite a London life.

1000
00:58:48,000 --> 00:58:51,320
-她在跟她的编辑约会  -是认真的吗
- She's seeing that publisher. - Is it serious?

1001
00:58:51,770 --> 00:58:56,520
他长得不差  而且还喘气
Well, he's not bad looking and he's still alive,

1002
00:58:56,550 --> 00:58:59,990
这样他与我们同龄的男士相比就有两项优势了
which puts him two points ahead of most men of our generation.

1003
00:59:01,140 --> 00:59:03,880
可是她能找个比他更好的
Which doesn't alter the fact she could do a great deal better.

1004
00:59:03,880 --> 00:59:07,200
-你了解他吗  -不怎么了解
- Do you know anything about him? - Not really.

1005
00:59:07,930 --> 00:59:10,910
我们在唐依阁的时候  他跟马修谈过
He talked to Matthew a bit when we were at Duneagle...

1006
00:59:17,400 --> 00:59:18,580
回房去吧
Go to bed.

1007
00:59:19,490 --> 00:59:20,680
你看起来很疲惫
You look done in.

1008
00:59:28,340 --> 00:59:30,410
明天的佃户午餐  您需要我去吗
Do you want me at the tenants' luncheon tomorrow?

1009
00:59:30,410 --> 00:59:32,340
你不必出席
No, there's no reason for you to be.

1010
00:59:33,260 --> 00:59:34,530
我知道您想保护我
I know you're trying to shield me...

1011
00:59:34,530 --> 00:59:36,520
让我用自己的方式来打理吧
Let me manage things in my own way.

1012
00:59:36,520 --> 00:59:39,370
听我的  这样最好
Please. It'll be for the best.

1013
00:59:41,270 --> 00:59:44,650
我也有想法的  马修和我以前常常谈...
I have ideas, you know. Matthew and I used to talk...

1014
00:59:44,650 --> 00:59:47,850
亲爱的  我知道我是对的
My dear, I know I'm right in this.

1015
00:59:49,060 --> 00:59:50,280
去睡吧
Now, go to bed.

1016
01:00:15,210 --> 01:00:16,110
小姐
My lady?

1017
01:00:16,110 --> 01:00:18,360
抱歉这么晚来打搅你
I'm sorry to bother you so late,

1018
01:00:19,420 --> 01:00:21,290
但我想你知道我为何事而来
but I think you know why I've come.

1019
01:00:23,100 --> 01:00:26,020
-我是来道歉的  -您不必道歉
- To apologise. - You have nothing to apologise for.

1020
01:00:26,030 --> 01:00:28,940
是我唐突了  说了不该说的话
I pushed into your room and I spoke impertinently.

1021
01:00:28,940 --> 01:00:32,280
我想你知道奶奶赞同你的观点
I suppose you know my grandmother agrees with you.

1022
01:00:32,280 --> 01:00:34,630
这我并不奇怪
That doesn't surprise me.

1023
01:00:36,120 --> 01:00:38,270
这么说  您是决定
So, does this mean you've decided

1024
01:00:38,270 --> 01:00:40,330
回到生活中来了吗
to return to the land of the living?

1025
01:00:41,410 --> 01:00:44,740
如果是这样  我很高兴
Because, if so, I'm glad.

1026
01:00:45,900 --> 01:00:47,110
我只是
It means that I

1027
01:00:47,850 --> 01:00:50,930
意识到我已经颓废消沉太久了
know that I've spent too long in the land of the dead.

1028
01:00:52,080 --> 01:00:55,680
我们都很喜欢卡劳利先生  小姐
We were very fond of Mr Crawley, you know, my lady.

1029
01:00:56,170 --> 01:00:57,370
我们所有人
All of us.

1030
01:00:58,470 --> 01:00:59,530
我
I...

1031
01:01:20,640 --> 01:01:22,840
哭吧  小姐
You cry, m'lady.

1032
01:01:23,560 --> 01:01:26,020
好好哭一场
You have a good cry.

1033
01:01:27,010 --> 01:01:29,230
现在该把眼泪都流出来
That's what's needed now.

1034
01:01:32,090 --> 01:01:33,850
等您准备好了
And when you're ready...

1035
01:01:34,910 --> 01:01:36,670
就可以做您该做的了
..You can get to work.

1036
01:01:37,580 --> 01:01:40,110
因为您很坚强
Because you are strong enough.

1037
01:01:45,780 --> 01:01:48,330
您能承受这份考验
You're strong enough for the task.

1038
01:01:48,860 --> 01:01:50,610
是吗  卡森
But am I, Carson?

1039
01:01:51,060 --> 01:01:54,260
问题就在这儿  爸爸似乎不这么想
That's the point. Papa doesn't seem to think so.

1040
01:01:54,310 --> 01:01:58,530
难道您不该为了卡劳利先生  保护他的遗志吗
Don't you owe it to Mr Crawley, to protect his work?

1041
01:01:58,610 --> 01:02:00,920
努力维护他所做出的变革
To fight for the changes he made?

1042
01:02:01,180 --> 01:02:04,250
让唐顿走上正确的道路
To steer Downton in the right direction?

1043
01:02:04,790 --> 01:02:06,440
我知道我怀疑自己的时候
I know I can always count on you

1044
01:02:06,450 --> 01:02:09,710
你肯定会为我鼓劲
for a draught of self-confidence whenever I start to doubt.

1045
01:02:09,980 --> 01:02:12,630
我永远都在这儿
And you will always find one here.

1046
01:02:16,080 --> 01:02:17,470
晚安  卡森
Good night, Carson.

1047
01:02:20,210 --> 01:02:21,660
晚安  小姐
Good night, m'lady.

1048
01:02:32,780 --> 01:02:34,300
我的天
Oh my gosh.

1049
01:02:38,210 --> 01:02:42,260
这是怎么了
Ohh... What in God's name...?

1050
01:02:42,260 --> 01:02:45,010
肯定是叉子放得不是地方
I must have put those ruddy prongs in wrong.

1051
01:02:45,010 --> 01:02:46,830
你肯定有什么没做对
You did something wrong.

1052
01:02:47,580 --> 01:02:49,970
今天可真够精彩的
What a day this has turned out to be.

1053
01:02:50,030 --> 01:02:51,020
怎么了
Why?

1054
01:02:51,050 --> 01:02:53,600
维斯特保姆被解雇了
Nanny West has been sacked.

1055
01:02:53,600 --> 01:02:55,180
明天有得说了
So, that's fun for tomorrow.

1056
01:02:55,180 --> 01:02:58,260
如果有人看见了这个我也得被解雇了
Well, I'll get the sack if anyone sees this!

1057
01:02:58,380 --> 01:03:01,340
让黛茜和艾薇早上来收拾吧
Let Daisy and Ivy clean it up in the morning.

1058
01:03:01,340 --> 01:03:04,180
哪能让黛茜知道我不会使用这个
But Daisy mustn't find out I don't know how to work it.

1059
01:03:04,180 --> 01:03:05,190
为什么
Why ever not?

1060
01:03:05,190 --> 01:03:06,980
那样她就是未来
Because it makes her part of the future

1061
01:03:06,980 --> 01:03:10,140
而我就被留在过去了  你还不明白吗
and leaves me stuck in the past, don't you see?

1062
01:03:13,090 --> 01:03:16,400
给我件围裙  我们一起收拾
Oh... Fetch me an apron. We'll do it together.

1063
01:03:16,400 --> 01:03:19,000
-真的吗  -有何不可
- Would you, really? - Why not?

1064
01:03:19,630 --> 01:03:21,140
睡觉有什么好
Who needs sleep?

1065
01:03:21,930 --> 01:03:23,150
谢谢
Thank you.

1066
01:03:29,520 --> 01:03:32,610
-我一直不是很喜欢她  -维斯特保姆吗
- I was never sure I liked her. - Nanny West?

1067
01:03:32,970 --> 01:03:35,540
虽然这事轮不到我说
It's not for me to have an opinion,

1068
01:03:35,590 --> 01:03:37,210
但我还是要说
but I will say this...

1069
01:03:55,420 --> 01:03:57,120
你昨晚去哪了
Where did you get to last night?

1070
01:03:57,580 --> 01:03:59,380
我进来之前我就睡着了
I was fast asleep before you came in

1071
01:03:59,380 --> 01:04:01,180
我走的时候你还在睡
and you were sleeping when I left.

1072
01:04:01,180 --> 01:04:03,100
我的确睡得很晚
I'm afraid it was very late.

1073
01:04:03,120 --> 01:04:06,100
但是你来得正好  我想告诉你
But I'm glad you're here now because I want you to know

1074
01:04:06,300 --> 01:04:10,570
我们真是要好好感谢巴罗
that we owe a great debt to Barrow, here.

1075
01:04:12,540 --> 01:04:15,060
我发现维斯特小姐非常不适合做保姆
It turns out Miss West is quite unsuited to the role of Nanny.

1076
01:04:15,060 --> 01:04:17,370
-她今天就走人  -什么  又是这样
- She is leaving today. - What? Not another one.

1077
01:04:17,380 --> 01:04:20,670
相信我  回头再说  我得走了  要迟了
Trust me. We'll talk about it later. I must run or I'll be late.

1078
01:04:21,820 --> 01:04:25,560
巴罗  我是真心的  谢谢你
Barrow, I meant what I said. Thank you.

1079
01:04:25,560 --> 01:04:27,360
我很高兴  夫人
I'm glad, your ladyship.

1080
01:04:27,570 --> 01:04:31,330
我就是觉得她不是那么称职
I just had a hunch that she wasn't quite all Sir Garnet.

1081
01:04:46,830 --> 01:04:49,530
这我不介意  你先测试一下就好
I've no problem, as long as you test them first.

1082
01:04:54,830 --> 01:04:56,730
真抱歉没能去迎接大家
I'm so sorry to miss your arrival.

1083
01:04:56,730 --> 01:04:59,090
没事  小姐  我们还没开席呢
That's all right, m'lady. We've not begun to eat.

1084
01:04:59,090 --> 01:05:01,750
-来坐这儿吧  -我就坐这儿就好
- Come and sit here. - I'll manage very well at the end.

1085
01:05:01,750 --> 01:05:03,870
卡森去给我搬个椅子来吧
Carson can find me a chair.

1086
01:05:04,580 --> 01:05:07,890
坐这儿吧  我去那边坐
No. Sit here. I'll go to the end.

1087
01:05:09,880 --> 01:05:11,150
这才是你该坐的地方
This is your place.

1088
01:05:12,290 --> 01:05:14,070
你真的有这个时间吗
Are you sure you have time for this?

1089
01:05:14,720 --> 01:05:15,480
当然
Quite sure.

1090
01:05:15,490 --> 01:05:17,460
我一直很期待呢
I've been looking forward to it.

1091
01:05:18,440 --> 01:05:19,780
泰勒先生
Now, Mr Taylor.

1092
01:05:19,780 --> 01:05:22,020
你说要放弃牧羊是怎么回事
What's all this I hear about your giving up sheep?

1093
01:05:22,020 --> 01:05:24,610
小姐  事情可不是那么简单
Well, m'lady, it's not quite as simple as that.

1094
01:05:24,610 --> 01:05:27,580
说实话  我宁可放牧
If truth be told, I'd rather be farming livestock...

1095
01:05:30,200 --> 01:05:31,550
为什么
And why is that?

1096
01:05:45,620 --> 01:05:50,560
下集预告

1097
01:05:45,890 --> 01:05:47,940
-我找到一封马修的信  -放在哪的
- There's a letter from Matthew. - Where was it?

1098
01:05:47,940 --> 01:05:49,560
放在办公室一本书里
Hidden in a book in the office.

1099
01:05:49,560 --> 01:05:51,600
你是想逃避真相吗
Are you trying to hide from the truth?

1100
01:05:51,610 --> 01:05:54,640
你更希望能独自经营唐顿
That you would prefer to be in sole charge of the estate.

1101
01:05:54,640 --> 01:05:57,330
布雷思韦特和安娜之间有些矛盾
There's bad feeling between Braithwaite and Anna.

1102
01:05:57,330 --> 01:05:59,160
-老爷  -安娜待她不太友善
- M'lord? - Anna has been a little unkind.

1103
01:05:59,160 --> 01:06:01,060
-什么那么好笑  -没什么  贝茨先生
- What's so funny? - Nothing, Mr Bates.

1104
01:06:01,060 --> 01:06:03,550
我想让汤姆来指导你
I want "Tom" to be your instructor.

1105
01:06:03,550 --> 01:06:05,710
我们做这些要瞒着爸爸吗
Are we to do all this without telling Papa?

1106
01:06:05,710 --> 01:06:08,650
待人接物  有些事不能说得太明白了
There can be too much truth in any relationship.

1107
01:06:08,650 --> 01:06:11,850
罗斯小姐问我能不能陪她去俱乐部
